1) intelligible command prompt: To get a command prompt that tells
what machine and directory you are in, append the
following line to your ~/.envfile or the ~/.profile
export PS1=[$(uname -n)]${PWD##*/}$

2) in order to access the history file and edding commands using the
arrow keys insert the following line into your ~/.profile:  
EDITOR=emacs


2) Free Software can be found at the www  site
ftp://sunsite.cnlab-switch.ch/mirror/aix
useful is 
monitor : reports cpu usage and machine usage (kmem is missing)
make    : GNU-make
emacs   : editor
dired   : to be usedwith emacs
